Choose the right test layer:
- prefer Vitest plus React Testing Library style coverage for focused unit and integration behavior
- prefer Playwright for async Server Component-heavy flows, server actions, auth journeys, streaming, cross-route flows, or browser-dependent behavior
- use behavior-level assertions instead of implementation-detail tests
- prefer accessible queries such as getByRole and getByLabelText for component tests
- use realistic user interactions instead of component internals
- in Playwright, prefer resilient locators like getByRole() and rely on built-in auto-waiting instead of manual sleeps

Assess test impact:
- decide whether the change needs new tests, updated tests, or only verification runs
- map changed files to likely affected test files
- keep new coverage focused on changed behavior

